issue.title: Custom environment support
issue.body:
### Clear and concise description of the problem

Jest supports running tests in custom environments using the [`testEnvironment` option](https://jestjs.io/docs/configuration#testenvironment-string). I'd like to have a similar feature in Vitest, both to make it easier to migrate from Jest to Vitest, and so users of [my custom environment](https://github.com/nickmccurdy/jest-environment-url) can use Vitest. This would also make it easier to support Vitest in the [Testing Library Recorder Extension](https://github.com/testing-library/testing-library-recorder-extension), since it uses my custom environment.

### Suggested solution

1. Support using custom strings with the `environment` option
   - Optionally, we could also support passing an environment class directly to the option
2. Support using custom strings with `@vitest-environment` (also `@jest-environment` for compatibility)
3. Resolve strings like `jsdom` to `vite-environment-jsdom` (or `jest-environment-jsdom` if we can figure out how to support Jest environments directly)

### Alternative

Use the [adapter pattern](https://sourcemaking.com/design_patterns/adapter) to load Jest environments instead of supporting them directly

### Additional context

_No response_

### Validations

- [X] Follow our [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)
- [X] Read the [Contributing Guidelines](https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md).
- [X] Read the [docs](https://vitest.dev/guide/).
- [X] Check that there isn't already an issue that request the same feature to avoid creating a duplicate.

comment.body:
> We can also move to classes and adapter pattern, of course, so it's easier to overwrite.

So are you suggesting an API similar to [`JestEnvironment`](https://github.com/facebook/jest/blob/2fa8763db2e661b520ebebeef45a22897d6da673/packages/jest-environment/src/index.ts#L40-L51)? Personally I'm not really a fan of this approach, as it encourages inheritance. Also, since Jest similarly runs tests in separate environments (using VMs instead of workers), the instances aren't really shared much outside of Jest's internal APIs.

issue.title: [DataCap Application] F3
issue.body:
# Large Dataset Notary Application

To apply for DataCap to onboard your dataset to Filecoin, please fill out the following.

## Core Information
- Organization Name: F3
- Website / Social Media: https://f3.xyz/  https://twitter.com/f3_f3xyz
- Total amount of DataCap being requested (between 500 TiB and 5 PiB):5PIB
- Weekly allocation of DataCap requested (usually between 1-100TiB):200TiB
- On-chain address for first allocation:f1jvsdgfwf3mo2knxwl6jlqm5oupufykd2ati6liq

_Please respond to the questions below by replacing the text saying "Please answer here". Include as much detail as you can in your answer._

## Project details

Share a brief history of your project and organization.
```
F3 is an NFT trading platform with 60 senior technical teams worldwide, 28K Twitter followers and 20K telegram followers. F3 issued the platform's NFT, and 300 copies of the genesis period have been sold out.

F3 enables users to discover and trade NFT products, and can also help creators to create and sell NFTs. F3 will provide a series of professional and free support for high-quality NFT products settled on the F3 platform.

F3 is very concerned about Filecoin. We plan to wait until the launch of FVM, and all NFT products on the F3 platform will be settled with FIL, becoming the world's only and largest NFT trading platform based on FIL settlement.
```

What is the primary source of funding for this project?
```
The founder of F3 owns a lot of BTC\ETH\FIL\usdt, etc., the economic strength is strong, and F3 has been able to achieve a certain degree of profitability
```

What other projects/ecosystem stakeholders is this project associated with?
```
No stakeholders, F3 is independent
```


## Use-case details

Describe the data being stored onto Filecoin
```
The F3 platform update is very fast. The data stored in the Filecoin network includes F3 product iteration and official website update data, new NFT products, F3 brand promotion, etc.
```

Where was the data in this dataset sourced from?
```
From F3 platform update data, NFT transaction data, NFT promotion data, and even Twitter space data
```

Can you share a sample of the data? A link to a file, an image, a table, etc., are good ways to do this. 
```
https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/11vfIx6ze4awBQL0tbDTzj-XaBK2ihilP?usp=sharing
https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1YtqSP1DvaM90A_TUWs0eAJcjpQClcnu-?usp=sharing
https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1Q9Yb7PYdh9xyo4EK_o3QB1K1PcR0qJBa?usp=sharing 
```

Confirm that this is a public dataset that can be retrieved by anyone on the Network (i.e., no specific permissions or access rights are required to view the data).
```
Confirm.
```

What is the expected retrieval frequency for this data?
```
This is our backup data, expected to be retrieved every 12 months.
```

For how long do you plan to keep this dataset stored on Filecoin?
```
about 12 -18 months
```


## DataCap allocation plan

In which geographies (countries, regions) do you plan on making storage deals?
```
We hope that more miners will store our data, they may come from any corner of the world, I hope these data can be safely stored
```

How will you be distributing your data to storage providers? Is there an offline data transfer process?
```
We do not have a clear limit on this. We think that if it is small data, it will be transmitted online. If it is large data, consider offline hard disk transmission.
```

How do you plan on choosing the storage providers with whom you will be making deals? This should include a plan to ensure the data is retrievable in the future both by you and others.
```
We will find storage providers through Slack, GitHub, etc. I hope these storage providers can cooperate with me when I need to retrieve
```

How will you be distributing deals across storage providers?
```
We will strictly abide by the rules of FIL+ to achieve decentralized storage.
```

Do you have the resources/funding to start making deals as soon as you receive DataCap? What support from the community would help you onboard onto Filecoin?
```
Yes, I do
```
